PEER TO PEER ARCHITECTURE:

- Individual computers (peers) act as both clients and servers.

Protocols:

1.WebRTC

- Stands for Web Real-Time Communication
- It uses UDP.
- Used for streaming like video class.
- Data loss in video calls is not a big issue.

TCP

- Connetion oriented
Flow:
   - It order the packets.
   - Create a virtual connetion with the server
   - Send the packets
   - Server receive the packet.
   - If dataloss occured client ack to the client
   - The client sent back to the server 
- Used when dataloss is matters

UDP

- Connectionless oriented
Flow:
   - There is no order in the packets 
   - Packets are sent randomly using multiple conntections at a time
- Dataloss occurs
- It is fast since it doesn't have single connection,no acknolegements. Thats why WebRTC is used.
